response:
We start by noticing that the moduli are pairwise coprime, so we can use the Chinese Remainder Theorem. First, we write the congruences in the form $x \equiv a \pmod{m}$: \begin{align*}
x &\equiv -1 \pmod{27} \\
x &\equiv -2 \pmod{125} \\
