\end{align*>The Chinese Remainder Theorem tells us that there is a unique solution modulo $27 \cdot 125 \cdot 343 = 1157625$. We can find this solution by solving the system of congruences. We start by solving the first two congruences. Since $27$ and $125$ are coprime, we can use the method of successive substitutions. We write $125$ as $1 \cdot 27 + 98$, so $125 = 4 \cdot 27 + 98$. Therefore, we have \begin{align*}
